{"id":"destroyer","term":"Destroyer","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 12:23\">Ex. 12:23</a>), the agent employed in the killing of the first-born; the destroying angel or messenger of God. (Comp. <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 19:35\">2 Kings 19:35</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 24:15\">2 Sam. 24:15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 24:16\">16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 78:49\">Ps. 78:49</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 12:23\">Acts 12:23</a>.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 12:23","2 Kings 19:35","2 Samuel 24:15","2 Samuel 24:16","Psalms 78:49","Acts 12:23"]}